comments:
Chemistry 101 discusses principles of chemistry for students with some basic knowledge of chemistry and calculus, focusing on understanding chemical reactions at the atomic and molecular level.

Students found the material covered in this course to be more interesting than they expected and reported gaining much knowledge. The textbook (Zumdahl) was reviewed favorably, and students found the online homework "very helpful in teaching the basic ideas," though "not at all useful for the exams."&#8232;&#8232;

Most student comments regarding the professor asserted that Professor Berry "conveys [his] knowledge" effectively and demonstrated a "complete understanding of the material." Students also complimented his engaging style, citing his "funny jokes" and enthusiasm for the subject matter. Professor Berry was judged to be accessible and understanding towards confused students, though some would have preferred a more organized teaching style. Berry did not follow the syllabus closely, which allowed for more thorough explanations of complex material, but left some students feeling "unsure of what to study." &#8232;

Students worked hard in this class, due to the difficulty of material. Many cited a desire for more assistance in locating materials to study and practice for exams.
